\nall models, the correlation between $\\gamma$-ray luminosity and spin-down power\nis consistent with a square root dependence. The $\\gamma$-ray luminosities\nobtained by using our beaming factors not exceed the spin-down power. This\nsuggests that assuming a beaming factor of one for all objects, as done in\nother studies, likely overestimates the real values. The data show a relation\nbetween the pulsar spectral characteristics and the width of the accelerator\ngap that is consistent with the theoretical prediction for the Slot Gap model.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 15 Mar 2014 20:26:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 19 Mar 2014 08:43:35 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 18 Nov 2014 19:23:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-02-11"}
