au_ph>>T_L/f. The acceleration term is\nindependent of the particle distance, r, and thus reduces the r-dependence of\n<w^2>^1/2 in the bidisperse case.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 16 Mar 2014 00:35:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 3 Jul 2014 17:12:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
