describe the spectrum of the probabilities of permutation equalities in a\nfinite group as $\\pi$ varies over all the elements of $S_{n}$. This spectrum\nturns-out to be closely related to the partition of $n!$ into a sum of the\ncorresponding Hultman numbers.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 16 Mar 2014 01:20:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 2 Oct 2014 18:07:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-10-03"}
